gomodel:SYNGO_5283  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5: \"Overexpressed Caskin1 was detected predominantly within the somatodendritic region of the transfected neurons, with local enrichment within the dendritic spine heads (Fig. 5F,G). Ultrastructural analyses in Caskin1-V5 and EGFP cotransfected neurons were processed by anti-V5 pre-embedding immunocytochemistry and visualized by DAB precipitates. Our results proved that overexpressed Caskin1 was indeed present in postsynaptic dendritic spines forming synapses (see Fig. 5E).\"\n\nFigure 7: in immunofluorescence imaging of Caskin-1 and -2 double-knockout mice, overexpressed EGFP-Caskin1 co-localized with endogenous Shank2 at dendritic spines.. Experimental description: M&M: \"CD1 (WT), C57Bl6/J (WT), Caskin dKO (Caskin1-/-/2-/-) and Caskin dHZ (Caskin1+/-/2+/-) transgenic mice were housed ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5283" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
